        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 22 at 4:47PM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 446 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Falfurrias Junior High School, or near Falfurrias, moving northwest
at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Premont, Concepcion, Ramirez, La Gloria, Rios, and Cruz Calle.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
